<p>
<seg id=1> In eastern India, a collision between a train and a bus at a rail crossing occurred near Danhad City in the state of Bihar, causing the death of ten people and injuring five. </seg>
<seg id=2> Railroad officials blamed the bus passengers for the accident, the Indian news agency India Press Trust report said. </seg>
<seg id=3> The report said that impatient passengers at the rail crossing seized the key from the crossing guard and opened the barrier. </seg>
<seg id=4> But before the bus had time to cross the track the train arrived, causing the collision. </seg>
<seg id=5> All of the fatalities were passengers on the bus. </seg>
